questions.questionText:
To start off, please confirm the following information:
- First and last name
- General Location (State/Province)

*Please also make sure to set your age, pronouns, and timezone using the Castbot buttons above*
Who referred you to Power Grab, if anyone? How did you hear about Power Grab?

**Power Grab is a fast-paced game lasting 18 days with an Elimination Ceremony almost every night at 10pm EST. We expect you to be present and active within the game.**

Do you foresee any conflicts or potential reasons you may not be able to fully participate? Are you playing any other games during the season time frame, and if so, will you be able to commit to Power Grab? 

On a scale of 1-5, with 1 being the least and 5 being the most, how active of a player do you expect to be?
Tell us about your ORG history! What ORG’s have you played in the last 2 years? How did you do in those ORG’s?
There are no direct competitions in Power Grab. Do you think you will thrive in this atmosphere? Why or why not?
What about the theme of the season in particular speaks to you?

Is there anyone in the community you **will not** play with? We want to provide a fun, safe, and enjoyable experience to the best of our ability. We will keep this information private between production and you. 

Please provide the first & last name of the player(s) as well as their discord handles or other handles/usernames (if you did not play with them on discord).

Please answer these three questions: 

1. Are you a cat person, a dog person, or both….or neither?

2. Pick the traits that fit you the best:
a. Loyal and Enthusiastic
b. Independent and Mysterious
c. Curious and Quirky
d. Adaptable and Unpredictable

3. When you are at a party, how likely are you to be the person in the following scenarios (please rate on a scale of 1-10)?
a. Hostess with the mostest, chatting everyone up
b. Hanging out with your small squad of homies in the corner, doing your own thing
c. Hiding in a room and only sneaking out for food and drink…your extroverted friends forced you to come
Please give us your final elevator pitch as to why you should be cast for Power Grab!

There are 2 things you must complete in order to finish your application! We need a photo and an interview.  

Please note that we **do** consider submitting a photo and an interview a prerequisite to applying for the game. You may submit additional photos later if you would like!

**Photo**
-Please submit a photo and make sure everything is in frame (see example below).
-Waist-up, make sure all body parts are in frame. Make sure the photo is good quality!
-We actually recommend that you do not include pets in your photo for the season (but if you would like to send separate photos of your pets, feel free!)

This video may also help- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KeIlXFmFu84.

**Interview**
You will need to schedule an interview with Production.

Deadline for your materials and interviews are on July 30th, however, we recommend submitting as early as possible in case we choose to cast earlier depending on the pool.

We highly encourage you to learn more about Power Grab by reading the rules here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1_y0Jdoma9JPCC13uHFOGbG-xb-KtyPjbIH9LSRI48dw/edit?usp=sharing.

If you have any questions, feel free to ping Production.

questions.questionText:
**__Welcome to PatORG S37. This is the interview portion of the application. Answer this at your convenience. Make sure to show off your amazing personality so we can get to know you!__** 

1. We want to know who **you** are! Please give us your name, age, pronouns, timezone, and give us any additional information about yourself that you think we’d love to know. Remember, this is our first impression of you.

2a. Do you have any experiences with ORGs? If so how did they go, do you have any confessionals, awards, funny moments, gameplay you would like to share? 

2b. If you haven't played an ORG, Which survivor player would you most likely play like and why? What part of this game do you think you would lack at and also be very strong at the most?
3. How will you approach this game? What would be your ideal strategy for playing this game?
4. Do you view yourself more as a selfless or a selfish player? What characteristics do you have that makes you think that you'd be more of whatever option you chose?
5. Do you think you would prefer a smaller cast or bigger cast? Why did you choose what you did vs the other option?
6. You’re leaving somebody out of the votes and it’s a huge blindside, how do you attempt to do damage control?
7. If you were to create a sketch for SNL, what would it be? Does not have to include any sort of dialogue, just a general idea!
8. Why should you be cast? **Make this your best answer!!**

questions.questionText: What is your name? Tell us a little about yourself! What are your hobbies, interests, pet peeves, etc? Please write as much as you want so we can get to know you!
Do you watch the show Survivor? If yes, what are some of your favorite seasons and players? Why are they your favorites?

Which archetype do you think fits you best as a player: challenge beast, social butterfly, or strategic mastermind? Why?
As a player, do you consider yourself to be more of a hero, villain, or neither? Why?

How active do you plan on being during the season? What times of day will you be the most active?

Whilst the occasional periods of inactivity due to real life is understandable, we have developed a reputation for casting consistently active players which benefits spectators, players' (and their games) and the hosting team.
Are you currently playing or applied to any other orgs that will overlap with our schedule? Do you have any in real life events planned that might interfere with the game for you?
If you had a time machine and could visit anywhere in the world, at any time in history, where and when would you visit?

Are there any accommodations you would like to request if cast (ex: colorblindness, dyslexia, etc.)? 

This will not in any way affect whether or not you are cast.
